notesStmt.note: Incipit: Omnes homines natura scire desiderant. Nam quaelibet res ferente natura appetit perfectionem...
Otherwise unknown according to bookseller's description, 1953.
Same commentary is found in UPenn Ms. Codex 763 (Zacour-Hirsch).

msContents.summary: Anonymous commentary on Aristotle's Metaphysics with an index to the Metaphysics.

supportDesc.extent: 85 leaves : 291 x 215 (233 x 133) mm. bound to 297 x 215 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper i (modern paper) + 85 + i (modern paper); [1-85]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 39-49 long lines; ruled in lead.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a Gothic cursive script by a single hand, with marginal annotations in a second hand.

decoDesc.decoNote: 3-line to 6-line initials with pink, red, blue, green, gray, and gold ornamentation, some with foliate extensions (f. 1r, 8v, 10v, 16v, 23v, 35r, 37v, 49r, 52v); simple 3-line red initials throughout, with rubrication used for capitals, underlining, and paragraph markers.

origin.p: Written in Germany in the 15th century (Zacour-Hirsch).
